text:
I just duplicated this bug on a fresh co of 1.4 on Win XP.  The URL Kupu sends
back to the browser is this:

    http://localhost:8888/default/authoring/index/kupupopups/image.html

But Keven Ages' proposed change doesn't fix the problem.  With Keven's changes
the URL Kupu sends back to the server becomes:

    http://localhost:8888/kupu/common/kupupopups/image.html

which is wrong now that Kupu is a module.  What the URL *should* be is this:

    http://localhost:8888/default/modules/kupu/kupu/common/kupupopups/image.html

except, of course, that the pub name shouldn't be hard-coded.  Who knows how to
handle this problem?  There was a similar problem with FCKeditor that I never
did resolve satisfactorily.

Note: Kevin Ages' attachment is still identical to the kupubasetools.js in the
trunk except for those 2 lines that he changed at line 535 and 722.  So here's
the patch he *would* have submitted (which DOES NOT WORK):

Index: C:/src/Lenya-1.4.x/src/modules/kupu/resources/kupu/common/kupubasetools.js
===================================================================
--- C:/src/Lenya-1.4.x/src/modules/kupu/resources/kupu/common/kupubasetools.js
(revision 41937)
+++ C:/src/Lenya-1.4.x/src/modules/kupu/resources/kupu/common/kupubasetools.js
(working copy)
@@ -532,7 +532,7 @@

     this.createLinkHandler = function(event) {
         /* create a link according to a url entered in a popup */
-        var linkWindow = openPopup('kupupopups/link.html', 300, 200);
+        var linkWindow = openPopup('/kupu/common/kupupopups/link.html', 300, 200);
         linkWindow.linktool = this;
         linkWindow.focus();
     };
@@ -719,7 +719,7 @@

     this.createImageHandler = function(event) {
         /* create an image according to a url entered in a popup */
-        var imageWindow = openPopup('kupupopups/image.html', 300, 200);
+        var imageWindow = openPopup('/kupu/common/kupupopups/image.html', 300,
200);
         imageWindow.imagetool = this;
         imageWindow.focus();
     };
